Comment:
Hi everyone!

It is time for game number 3 which also ended in a loss.  This time, at least my opponent had to sacrifice material to get at Henry.  I took a free pawn because I could not see that there was any immediate mate threat.  However, taking the pawn led to an exchange sacrifice which I had to accept or be a piece for two pawns light.  After having this material deficit in my game against Janet and losing to her in the manner I did I decided to accept the sacrifice and make Dongoodman prove its soundness.  Unfortunately he did exactly that and Henry ended up ..... well ..... erm ..... you will just have to follow this link and find out! http://gameknot.com/analyze-board.pl?bd=18572637&fb=1&rnd=0.2366468098222443.

At least f7 would have been guarded and RxP would really have won a pawn and not allowed the disaster that was to follow.  Mind you, Dongoodman may well have backed up his pawn if I had moved the other rook to d8.

31. ...... gxh6 - so the knights disappear from the board and so does my rook.  Sadly so does Henry's pawn shelter.  Henry has been totally denuded and needs a whole new wardrobe, never mind those medieval stockings.  But Glenda will not have time to cast the first stich or fill in the order form for a new wardrobe from MFI.  The Wicked Witch of the West and the WR on f1 will keep Henry so confined that he will not even be able to attempt a Deadly Dash despite having a few large, juicy, crevettes for lunch which has done wonders for his fitness!  At 64 he should be putting his feet up in his castle and not be dashing around that battlefield.  That is 18 year old Glenda's job!
